UBC9_SCHPO - Also known as ubc9. Experimental evidence at protein level: Swiss-Prot protein existence level 1. Catalyzes the covalent attachment of ubiquitin-like protein SUMO/Smt3 to other proteins. Required for efficient recovery from DNA damage or S-phase arrest and normal mitosis. This may be as part of a checkpoint independent recovery process. From Schizosaccharomyces pombe (strain 972 / ATCC 24843) (Fission yeast).
